DataElement.preferredDefinition: The property of being measured and described using two orthogonal directions.:Having, relating to, or consisting of more than one individual, element, part, or other component; manifold. (dictionary.com):The precise location of something; a spatially limited location._A mark that is long relative to its width; a length (straight or curved) without breadth or thickness; the trace of a moving point.:The dimension between two surfaces of an object, usually the smallest dimension as opposed to the width or the length: also, viscous consistency._Character string datatype stands for text data.
